{
  "text": "Another study of miR-125b in ccRCC revealed that miR-125b is under-expressed in metastatic tumors, based on the microarray results of 18 patients (23). However, Fu et al [CITATION_1] demonstrated that miR-125b was upregulated in ccRCC based on 276 samples by ISH, and higher expression of miR-125b predicted shorter survival time and a higher rate of recurrence. The two studies about miR-125b in ccRCC, including the present study, are limited, since the cases were collected from a single institute or area, which could not exclude the bias of area.",
